  "body": "# Problem\n\nCurrently whenever we compose a message and instead of sending it we go back to chats tab, we correctly save whatever we wrote in this chat as a draft. However it's not indicated in the Chats tab, making this actually cool feature go unnoticed and impossible to keep track of.\n\n## Implementation\n\nFor each chat with a drafted message, we show a text label in list item preview, simply saying it's a pending Draft, followed by whatever was typed inside the chat text input, like so\n\n<img width=\"375\" alt=\"Cell\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/57008342-b0dadd00-6bef-11e9-8e71-829f3641c48e.png\">\n\nThe text label uses the same text attributes with a different, Accent Blue, colour. It persists as long as the draft is composed until the input is either cleared or message sent.\n\nFigma -> [Drafts](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=2340%3A2)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nImplemented according to design and tested.\n\n## Notes\n\nThank you üôè  if you need help to visualise it, Telegram does something similar",
